# Joins in SQL

## Introduction
Joins in SQL are used to combine data from multiple tables based on related columns.

In real-world databases, information is usually stored across different tables to reduce duplication and improve organization.

Examples:
- Customers table stores customer details  
- Orders table stores purchase details  
- Employees table stores employee data  
- Departments table stores department names  

Joins allow us to connect these tables and retrieve meaningful combined information.

---

# Why Joins are Important
Joins help:
- Combine related data from multiple tables
- Build complete reports
- Reduce duplicate storage
- Improve database normalization
- Support real-world business queries

Without joins, relational databases lose much of their power.

