# Common Mistakes

## Mistake 1: Missing ON Condition
```sql
SELECT * FROM customers
JOIN orders;
```

Can create unwanted combinations.

---

## Mistake 2: Wrong Join Type
Using INNER instead of LEFT may hide unmatched records.

---

## Mistake 3: Ambiguous Column Names
Use table names or aliases:
```sql
customers.customer_id
```

---

# Best Practices

## 1. Always Use Proper ON Conditions
Prevents incorrect matches.

---

## 2. Use Aliases
Improves readability.

---

## 3. Choose Correct Join Type
Depends on business need.

